# ğŸ¤– Automated FAQ Assistant (n8n + OpenAI + Pinecone)

This project is an **AI-powered FAQ assistant** built with **n8n**.  
It automatically reads FAQ files uploaded to Google Drive, stores them in a vector database, and assists clients with instant answers via chat.  

---

## ğŸš€ How It Works

### ğŸ“‚ 1. Build the Knowledge Base
- **Google Drive Trigger** â†’ starts when a new FAQ file is uploaded.  
- **Download File** â†’ fetches the uploaded FAQ document.  
- **Default Data Loader** â†’ extracts text from the document.  
- **Recursive Character Text Splitter** â†’ breaks large text into small chunks.  
- **OpenAI Embeddings** â†’ converts text chunks into embeddings (numerical vectors).  
- **Pinecone Vector Store** â†’ saves embeddings in a vector database for semantic search.  

---

### ğŸ’¬ 2. Assist the Client
- **When Chat Message Received** â†’ trigger when a client sends a question.  
- **OpenAI Embeddings** â†’ convert the clientâ€™s question into an embedding.  
- **Pinecone Vector Store (Search)** â†’ find the most relevant FAQ chunks.  
- **AI Agent (OpenAI Chat Model)** â†’ generate a polite, professional response using the retrieved FAQ context.  
- **Send Back Response** â†’ the client instantly receives an accurate answer.  

